EDIT: One out of three times that you order from this place they will forget something. It’s usually chips or the salsa or both. I originally did not complain about it because they’ve always done the right thing and either brought me the item or refunded me for the chips and salsa. Once again, they forgot the chips, I gave them the option to deliver me the chips or refund me the chips and salsa (The salsa is useless without the chips). This time, they decided to be cheap and only refunded $1.50. I explained that I order from there twice a week, but the lady on the phone insinuated that I’m just trying to get free food. So not only have they raised their prices in the past few months but the service has also gone down hill. #sad  **original post** I come here for the quesadillas and the salsa. Both are easily the best in the neighborhood. I’m not sure why the other places can’t figure out how to simply make a good quesadilla. A bonus is that this place also has the best prices.

Vegan “short ribs” burrito was incredible. Best tex-mex I’ve had in NYC. Very quick and service was great. You can do call-in, order online, or walk-in. For walk-in, the cashier is located way at the back (about 15 ft away) and they have a card reader up front, which is nice for everyone to feel safer. Thank you all!

Great burrito! Mad it was good! Soft tortilla and great fillings! Way way better than Chipotle!!! I’m not really familiar with Mexican food, and I feel like after this one I have new standards for good burritos! Definitely come and try! Quick service! Right next to Franklin Avenue subway station

I loved my order, I inhaled my food...so no pictures this time. The carnita burrito, it was so juicy and every bite was a joy. Like I was legit sad when I finished. Chips and guac are on point too. The vegan tres leches is pretty good, if you like coconut (which I do).

This place is great. They hold true to their claim that they bring Southern California style Mexican food to NYC. Burritos are well wrapped, guac portions are very generous and their habanero salsa is on point.  Delivery is fast and the food is delicious and well seasoned. Overall an awesome experience.

On July 14th at 12:15pm I received a text response from Steven regarding my application for the restaurant associate position on Indeed. As this was a Sunday, I was unable to respond to him until about 10:00pm that evening. I was spending quality time with my family and just did not get to see my phone until later on in the evening. When I responded via text, I immediately received a call from Steven. Since I was driving home, I asked if it was okay to speak at a later time. He said it was okay and rudely hung up. Literally a second later, he texted me saying “Honestly if you want the job you should speak now, I will not be calling you back”. Please keep in mind that it was TEN in the night and he did not respond to my text asking me if it was okay to give me a call at said time. I will be attaching the images so that you can all read for yourself. I believe Steven is the owner. He is VERY unprofessional and it sucks because I had heard amazing things about this establishment. Please be prepared for this if you are planning on applying.

Breakfast burritos can not be beat!   Try the Chorizo one.   With the AM burritos, they're pre-prepped and ready to go, so you can stop in, get what you want, and be on your way within two minutes.   They always taste fresh and flavorful and the portions are huge.   I also like the salsa choices.   So happy to have a breakfast option that isn't a bagel in Crown Heights.   Staff is also really friendly and easy to chat with.   Happy for such a great local business in the neighborhood!

After walking by a few times, I decided to pop in for dinner. The Grilled Chicken Bay burrito (Chicken, Rice, Beans, Cheese, Guacamole, Sour Cream & Salsa) was good-smelling and good tasting. The chicken was tasty and well-seasoned, and there was plenty o' sour cream. The staff honored my request to get the guacamole on the side, and answered my questions patiently. The menu (available online, in case you want to check it out before going) has several options, I'll be sure to work my way through the list!  Takeout only. No tables. Delivery is available.
